# Svelte 5 Cursor Rules

## Runes (Svelte 5)
- Use `$state()` for reactive state declarations
- Use `$derived()` for computed values
- Use `$effect()` for side effects (replaces `$:` reactive statements)
- Use `$props()` for component props
- Use `$bindable()` for two-way binding props

## Component Patterns
- Use `{#snippet}` blocks for reusable template fragments
- Use `{@render}` to render snippets
- Prefer composition over inheritance
- Keep components focused and under 200 lines

## SvelteKit
- Use `+page.svelte` for pages, `+layout.svelte` for layouts
- Use `+page.server.ts` for server-side data loading
- Use form actions for mutations (progressive enhancement)
- Use `+error.svelte` for error pages

## Performance
- Svelte compiles away the framework — minimal runtime overhead
- Use `{#key}` blocks to force re-creation of elements
- Use `transition:` directives for animations
- Avoid unnecessary reactivity — only use `$state` for values that change
